\begin_layout Standard
Optimal information disclosure must balance two opposing forces – letting
 the participants to find the preferred matches, and alleviating the cream-skimm
ing behavior leading to low matching rates.
 On the one hand, more information about buyer characteristics allows the
 sellers to form the matches that they value the most.
